[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    23[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThe Python companion is structurally faithful to the main recipe's six pseudocode steps and the architectural picture (normalize NPPES, normalize internal record, multi-pass blocking against the registry, per-field comparators feeding a Fellegi-Sunter combiner with hard filters, three-bucket routing with a margin requirement, and attach-plus-schedule with drift-snapshot persistence). The Decimal-at-the-DynamoDB-boundary discipline is consistent with [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m_serialize_for_dynamodb[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, S3 keys do not carry leading slashes, the routing thresholds and margin are exposed as configuration, the per-field comparators handle the registry-specific patterns the recipe enumerates (legal-name change via the [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mother_names[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m field, license-number-plus-state as the strongest signal, taxonomy parent-class match, credential subset match), and the hard filters (deactivation, type mismatch, license-state mismatch) correctly drop categorical exclusions before scoring. The [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m_double_metaphone[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m helper now carries an explicit caveat in its docstring acknowledging that [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mjellyfish.metaphone[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m is the original metaphone, not double metaphone, which is an improvement over recipe 5.1's silent mislabeling.[K
